{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"626654c5-ec09-4773-97ad-5cccfa309f1a","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Dropped TFMs in MSTest v3:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported. Migrate to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`net5.0`** — not supported. Migrate to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`net462`** — still supported ✅\n\n**Package changes in MSTest v3:**\nThe separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are consolidated into a single **`MSTest`** meta-package.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd update your `.csproj` roughly like this:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7e12d99b-5831-4382-841c-de9f2e927587","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me recall what I know:\n\nMSTest v3 requires:\n- .NET 6.0 or later (for .NET Core/5+)\n- .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later\n\nSo the issues here:\n1. `net5.0` - .NET 5 is out of support and MSTest v3 dropped support for it. Users need to move to `net6.0` or later.\n2. `netcoreapp3.1` - .NET Core 3.1 is out of support and MSTest v3 dropped support for it.\n\n\n3. `net462` - This is the minimum supported version for MSTest v3, so it should work fine.\n\nAlso worth noting that MSTest v3 consolidated the package structure, so users should use the single `MSTest` meta-package instead of managing separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages.","outputTokens":513,"requestId":"4809:286947:600A7AD:68681F6:69FBFD3C"},"id":"3248a98a-166a-4784-ad70-02cd5ace9a4f","timestamp":"2026-05-07T02:47:34.260Z","parentId":"8af1f144-c554-44c6-a38a-3de9dd8f9a1c"}
